The paper deals with the problem of reconstructing a sparse signal from quantized compressive measurements, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. However, based on the abstract and the title, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the fundamental limits of data compression, communication, and storage. The paper proposes a new algorithm for quantized compressed sensing, which involves quantization of the measurements, and hence falls under the scope of cs.SP (Signal Processing). The paper also mentions the use of iterative algorithms and thresholding, which are common techniques in machine learning and optimization, and hence could be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.MM (Mathematical Optimization). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed algorithm on several quantization scenarios, which could involve image or video data, and hence could be classified under cs.CV (Computer Vision).
